frameDefinitions: An Agent manipulates a Sound_maker or a Cause causes the Sound_maker to emit a sound.
An Agent ceases an Activity without completing it. ''
In this frame a Speaker ceases speaking, sometimes about a particular Topic.
An Entity loses moisture with the outcome of being in a dry state.
Generally without overall (translational) motion,  an Agent places a Theme at a location, the Goal, which is profiled.
An Agent causes a Speaker to become silent, sometimes about a particular Topic.
frameExamples: The monks would <t>ring</t> the bell until sundown.
After the lawsuit, the company <t>stopped</t> producing the once very profitable toy.
Finally, Jan <t>shut</t> <t>up</t> about his car accident.
David <t>placed</t> his briefcase on the floor.
listRoleDefinitions: The individual that manipulates a Sound_maker so that it makes Noise.
The entity that produces the Noise, as a result of the action of the Agent.
The inanimate force of nature that causes the <fen>Sound_maker</fen> to produce noise.
The time at which the noise is produced.
The location at which the sound is produced.
This role identifies <fen>Agent</fen> that stops the <fen>Activity</fen>.

This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> stops the <fen>Activity</fen>.
The <fen>Speaker</fen> has previously been speaking but has now stopped.
The <fen>Expressor</fen> is the <fen>Speaker</fen>'s voice or other communicative noise emitted by the <fen>Speaker</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the becoming silent occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> is the location where the becoming silent occurs.
The <fen>Entity</fen> is the thing that loses moisture and becomes dry.
When the <fen>Entity</fen> becomes dry.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> becomes dry.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person (or other force) that causes the <fen>Theme</fen> to move.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the object that changes location during the Placing.
The role <fen>Goal</fen> is the location where the <fen>Theme</fen> ends up. This role is profiled by words in this frame.
<fen>Time</fen> is when the Placing occurs
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the Placing occurs.
The Agent is the person performing the intentional act.
The sentient entity that is not communicating.
The <fen>Expressor</fen> is the <fen>Speaker</fen>'s voice or other communicative noise emitted by the <fen>Speaker</fen>.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
listRoleExamples: <fex>You</fex> can ring the bell as often as you'd like.
<fex>The waiter</fex> placed the food on the table.
The waiter placed <fex>the food</fex> on the table.
